Acronym Finder

This simple program is used as an exercice to illustrate several important programming concepts on the Android platform.

It shows:
* how to perform an HTTP request on the Internet
* how to parse an XML response
* how to use Material Design
* how to use a Service to encapsulate long-duration operations
* how to use a Content Provider with an SQLite database to implement a cache in order to avoid overload on the network

 Finder

This simple program is used as an exercice to illustrate several important programming concepts on the Android platform.

It shows:
* how to perform an HTTP request on the Internet
* how to parse an XML response
* how to use Material Design
* how to use a Service to encapsulate long-duration operations
* how to use a Content Provider with an SQLite database to implement a cache in order to avoid overload on the network

 
